    <center><table class="itemDisplayTable">
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Title:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">A Project Report On Health Monitoring System And Wireless Transmission Of Parameters</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Authors:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">Pradhan, Siddhant<br />Subhankari das, Soumya<br />Saha, Sukanya</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Keywords:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">On Health Monitoring System<br />Wireless Transmission of Parameters</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Issue Date:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">1-May-2013 </td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Publisher:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">Srm University</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Series/Report no.:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">P6107</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Abstract:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">Wireless-sensor-network-based home monitoring system for elderly welfare involves functional monitoring of persons by introducing physiological parameter monitoring sub-system and remote operation of personal appliances by the elderly. In our project, we have implemented 4 modules.
First module consists of bio-sensors measuring physiological parameters for determining wellness.This module consists of bio sensors such as heart beat sensor, temperature sensor, MEMS sensor. Microcontroller retrieves all the information from the different sensors and sends this information to another remote system through zigbee module. This information will be viewed in Personal computer using VisualBasic.
The second module consists of personal appliances that are controlled by the elderly using a RF module.This module is the appliance section. It consists of different appliances such as be lamp, fan which can be operated by the elderly people from their bed. The switches to these devices are located in the 1st module kit.When the switches for respective devices are triggered, the PIC microcontroller sends the triggering signal to the transceiver which encodes the information and sends it to the receiver at the other end where the devices are located. Here the information is decoded and send to the 8051 microcontroller which in turn controls the relay unit to operate the respective devices .
The third module consists of zigbee module, serial communication, and a computer system which serves as the front end. The information sent by the bio sensors such as heart beat sensor, temperature sensor and MEMS sensors are retrieved by the PIC Microcontroller and are sent to the front end, which the doctors use to monitor the elderly personâ€™s health conditions, through zigbee module.
The fourth module is the GSM module which is connected to the computer system which serves as the front end with the purpose of sending a message to a particular person on his cell phone when a parameter shoots up and exceeds the normal setpoint automatically.This would help in rendering immediate aid to the patient irrespective of the presence of people around him</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">URI:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue"><a href="http://hdl.handle.net/123456789/17423">http://hdl.handle.net/123456789/17423</a></td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Appears in Collections:</td><td class="metadataFieldValue"><a href="/dspace/handle/123456789/17097">ICE-2013</a><br/></td></tr>
</table></center><br/>
